    <h1 style="text-align: center;">⚠️ Health Risks Preview</h1><br>
    <ul style="font-size: 20px; padding: 0 60px; line-height: 1.8;">
      <li>
        <b>Dehydration:</b> Affects physical and mental performance. <br>
        <strong>Signs:</strong> Dark urine, dry mouth, fatigue, dizziness<br>
        <strong>Prevention:</strong> Track fluid intake with TrackMyFit. Drink water at regular intervals.<br>
        <strong>Range:</strong> <em>Less than 1.5L/day is considered inadequate</em>
      </li><br>
      <li>
        <b>Malnutrition:</b> Results from a diet lacking essential nutrients.<br>
        <strong>Signs:</strong> Weak immunity, poor concentration, underweight or low BMI (< 18.5)<br>
          <strong>Prevention:</strong> Eat nutrient-dense meals and track with our daily intake dashboard.
      </li><br>
      <li>
        <b>Junk Food Overconsumption:</b> High in sugar, salt, and trans fats.<br>
        <strong>Risks:</strong> Obesity, Type 2 diabetes, heart disease, mood swings<br>
        <strong>Tip:</strong> Limit junk food to once or twice a week. Replace with fruit, nuts, or yogurt.
      </li><br>
      <li>
        <b>Obesity (High BMI > 25):</b> Increases the risk of heart disease, joint problems, and hypertension.<br>
        <strong>Suggestion:</strong> Track BMI with TrackMyFit and aim for 150 minutes of weekly activity.
      </li><br>
      <li>
        <b>Eye Strain:</b> Especially common with digital screens.<br>
        <strong>Prevention:</strong> Use the 20-20-20 rule (every 20 mins, look at something 20 feet away for 20 secs),
        and take regular breaks.<br>
        <strong>Check:</strong> Use TrackMyFit's online eye test tools.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>




